on_planning.py:201:            first_plan = resolve_manifest_validation_plan(\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:207:            second_plan = resolve_validation_plan(\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:219:                    \"numerical_sanity\",\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:220:                    \"morphology_sanity\",\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:221:                    \"circuit_sanity\",\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:222:                    \"task_sanity\",\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:308:                resolve_manifest_validation_plan(\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:334:                resolve_manifest_validation_plan(\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:353:                resolve_manifest_validation_plan(\ntests/test_validation_planning.py:378:                resolve_manifest_validation_plan(\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:16:from flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_contract import (\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:72:                per_root[303][\"realized_morphology_class\"],\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:76:                per_root[303][\"policy_evaluation\"][\"recommended_morphology_class\"],\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:139:                        \"reference_morphology_class\": \"surface_neuron\",\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:186:                root_summary[\"reference_morphology_class\"],\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:199:            \"default_morphology_class\": \"point_neuron\",\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:201:                {\"root_id\": 101, \"morphology_class\": \"surface_neuron\"},\ntests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py:263:                    \"minimum_morphology_class\": \"surface_neuron\",\ntests/test_baseline_execution.py:139:                arm_plan[\"circuit_assets\"][\"selected_root_assets\"][0][\"edge_bundle_paths\"][0][\"path\"]\ntests/test_baseline_execution.py:248:        \"circuit_assets\": {\ntests/test_baseline_execution.py:251:            \"circuit_asset_hash\": \"fixture_circuit_hash\",\ntests/test_baseline_execution.py:265:                    scope=\"circuit_output\",\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:10:## FW-M12-001 - Freeze a versioned readout-analysis contract, task taxonomy, and Milestone 12 design note\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:20:Define a library-owned Milestone 12 readout-analysis contract and publish a concise design note that locks the metric taxonomy. The contract should distinguish among shared comparison readouts, derived task readouts, wave-only diagnostics, and experiment-level comparison outputs; define stable metric IDs, units, scopes, required source artifacts, and canonical discovery helpers; and state which quantities are allowed to depend only on shared readouts versus which may consume wave-only patch or phase artifacts. The design note should stay tightly aligned with the locked Milestone 1 hypothesis, the T4a/T5a terminal readout boundary, and the existing `simulator_result_bundle.v1` invariants, while also naming the first task families, null-test hooks, and UI-facing outputs Milestone 12 must support.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:23:- There is one canonical readout-analysis contract in library code with explicit identifiers and normalization helpers for shared readout metrics, derived task metrics, wave-only diagnostics, and experiment-level comparison outputs.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:43:The manifest and planning layers already carry `primary_metric`, `companion_metrics`, output targets, comparison arms, and timebase information, but they still do not resolve those declarations into one normalized task-analysis plan. There is no canonical place to define which readouts are active for a run, which stimulus windows should be analyzed, how ON versus OFF or preferred versus null conditions should be paired, how seed sweeps roll up into experiment-level task summaries, or which null tests are required for a given experiment. Without a shared planning surface, later analysis scripts will reinterpret manifest intent differently, duplicate compatibility checks, and quietly disagree about what one “task metric” actually consumed.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:46:Extend the library-owned manifest and config normalization path so a manifest plus local config resolves into a deterministic Milestone 12 analysis plan. The normalized plan should identify active readouts, derived task-readout recipes, analysis windows, condition-pair definitions, comparison groups, seed-aggregation rules, null-test declarations, and declared output targets for both per-run and experiment-level outputs. Keep the representation explicit enough that execution, offline analysis, readiness workflows, and later UI work can all discover the same analysis intent without inventing separate script-local configuration schemes.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:50:- The normalized plan records active shared readouts, derived task-readout recipes, analysis windows, condition-pair or arm-pair definitions, null-test declarations, and seed-aggregation rules needed by Milestone 12 workflows.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:88:## FW-M12-004 - Implement motion-vector and optic-flow task decoders on a fair, canonical task interface\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:92:- Area: task decoders / motion estimation / analysis APIs\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:95:Milestone 12 explicitly calls for optic-flow estimates and motion-vector estimates, but the repo still has no decoder layer that can turn multi-condition readout evidence into a task-level motion estimate. The current vertical slice is still centered on a local motion patch and T4a/T5a terminal readouts, which is fine, but there is no shared interface that says how a decoder consumes shared readouts, stimulus metadata, or retinotopic context to produce a motion estimate without granting the wave model a special-purpose downstream decoder unavailable to the baselines. Without a canonical task-decoder layer, these metrics will either stay unimplemented or appear as one-off analysis code that is impossible to compare fairly.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:98:Build the first library-owned task-decoder interface for Milestone 12 and ship deterministic motion-vector and optic-flow estimators through that interface. The implementation should consume only declared shared readouts plus the normalized task-analysis plan and any allowed local context such as stimulus direction labels or retinotopic geometry metadata, and it should emit explicit task outputs with stable units, conventions, and diagnostic metadata. Support the current local motion-patch vertical slice first, but keep the interface extensible enough that later larger-field optic-flow tasks can reuse it without changing the contract.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:101:- There is a canonical task-decoder API that consumes normalized task inputs and emits deterministic motion-vector and optic-flow outputs with explicit units and conventions.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:103:- The implementation fails clearly when the manifest or result bundle does not provide enough directional or retinotopic context to realize the requested task metric.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:104:- The resulting task outputs are compatible with the Milestone 12 analysis contract and discoverable through shared helpers rather than hidden inside one report generator.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:109:- A focused task-decoder test module that feeds known directional fixtures through the canonical decoder interface and asserts deterministic motion-vector or optic-flow estimates plus clear failure behavior\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:112:Assume `FW-M12-001` through `FW-M12-003`, the Milestone 8 stimulus and retinal contracts, and the locked Milestone 1 fairness rules are already in place. The key guardrail is that task decoders may be richer than raw readouts without becoming wave-only cheats. Do not attempt to create a git commit as part of this ticket.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:118:- Area: wave diagnostics / spatial analysis / morphology-aware metrics\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:124:Implement the reusable Milestone 12 wave-diagnostic kernels that consume wave-capable result bundles and emit deterministic morphology-aware metrics. Reuse the existing Milestone 10 inspection logic where it already provides a good starting point, but refactor the relevant computations into contract-backed analysis functions that can be called by offline reports, experiment-level comparison workflows, and later UI data preparation. Keep these diagnostics explicitly separate from the shared comparison readout catalog so fairness remains visible: they are allowed wave-only diagnostics, not hidden replacements for the shared readout surface.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:140:## FW-M12-006 - Build experiment-level comparison orchestration, null tests, seed aggregation, and at least one automated task score\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:144:- Area: comparison workflows / task layer / experiment analytics\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:147:Per-run simulator bundles and per-run metrics tables already exist, but Milestone 12 is not complete until baseline-versus-wave comparisons become quantitative at the experiment level. Right now there is no library-owned workflow that loads the deterministic bundle set for one manifest, groups the intended arm comparisons, aggregates across seed sweeps, evaluates geometry-sensitive null tests, or emits a clean task-level summary that says whether the wave model changed a shared observable in the way the roadmap actually cares about. Without that orchestration layer, the repo can produce traces and metric rows forever without ever turning them into a task metric that tests the hypothesis.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:150:Implement the Milestone 12 task-layer workflow that loads normalized analysis plans plus local result bundles and emits experiment-level comparison outputs. The workflow should compare baseline versus `surface_wave`, intact versus shuffled, and where available `P0` versus `P1`; aggregate repeated seeds deterministically; run declared null tests and sanity checks; and compute at least one automated task score aligned with the locked Milestone 1 evidence ladder. Make the result explicit enough that later Milestone 13 validation and Milestone 14 UI work can consume the same experiment summary rather than reverse-engineering multiple bundle directories by hand.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:154:- The workflow records comparison pairing, seed aggregation, null-test outcomes, and at least one automated task score aligned with the Milestone 1 hypothesis, such as a geometry-sensitive null-direction suppression or latency effect that is tracked across intact versus shuffled or baseline-strength comparisons.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:157:- Regression coverage includes at least one fixture experiment with multiple arms and seed runs that asserts deterministic task summaries, null-test flags, and comparison grouping.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:161:- A smoke-style fixture workflow that loads multiple deterministic result bundles, runs the experiment-level task-analysis pipeline, and asserts stable comparison summaries plus at least one automated task score\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:164:Assume `FW-M12-001` through `FW-M12-005`, the Milestone 9 result-bundle contract, and the Milestone 10 execution workflow are already in place. This ticket is the core of the task layer: traces become experiment-level evidence here. Do not attempt to create a git commit as part of this ticket.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:173:The current simulator workflow writes per-run bundles with generic metrics and a lightweight UI comparison payload, but it still does not package Milestone 12 analysis outputs in a stable, discoverable way. There is no canonical experiment-level analysis bundle, no durable export format for task summaries, null-test tables, heatmap-like matrices, or phase-map references, and no agreed payload shape that later UI work can consume without reparsing raw metric rows. Without a packaging layer, Milestone 12 outputs will sprawl across ad hoc JSON, CSV, and HTML files that later readiness or dashboard work cannot discover reliably.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:176:Add the standard packaging and export layer for Milestone 12 outputs. Define deterministic output locations and shared discovery helpers for experiment-level analysis artifacts, extend the existing UI-facing payloads so they can reference task summaries and analysis visualizations, and ship at least one lightweight offline report or visualization entrypoint that proves the packaged outputs are reviewable outside notebooks. Preserve the existing `simulator_result_bundle.v1` invariants for per-run artifacts while layering Milestone 12 exports on top through explicit metadata and discovery rather than filename guessing.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:181:- The UI-facing payload story is extended so later Milestone 14 code can discover task summaries, comparison cards, and analysis visualizations without reparsing raw bundle directories.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:199:Even if the earlier Milestone 12 tickets land individually, the repo still needs one explicit integration pass showing that readout analysis, task decoding, wave diagnostics, comparison orchestration, export packaging, and UI-facing payloads actually work together as one coherent layer. Without a dedicated readiness ticket, it will be too easy to stop at isolated metric kernels or one successful report while leaving behind hidden contract mismatches, fairness regressions, broken discovery paths, or analysis outputs that only work for a single hand-crafted fixture.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:206:- The verification pass checks contract compatibility across analysis-plan resolution, shared-readout kernels, task decoders, wave-diagnostic kernels, experiment-level comparison orchestration, packaged exports, and UI-facing payload discovery.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:207:- The readiness report summarizes what was verified, what remains risky or deferred, and whether Milestone 12 is ready to support the Milestone 13 validation ladder and Milestone 14 dashboard work.\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:213:- `python3 scripts/run_agent_tickets.py --tickets-file agent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md --ticket-id FW-M12-008 --dry-run --runner true`\nagent_tickets/milestone_12_readouts_task_layer_tickets.md:217:This ticket should run after the earlier Milestone 12 tickets are complete. The main deliverable is confidence: one place where a reviewer can see that readouts, task metrics, null tests, wave diagnostics, packaging, and UI handoff all agree on the same experiment story. Do not attempt to create a git commit as part of this ticket.\ntests/test_task_decoder_analysis.py:25:from flywire_wave.task_decoder_analysis import (\ntests/test_task_decoder_analysis.py:28:    compute_task_decoder_analysis,\ntests/test_task_decoder_analysis.py:29