|\ndocs/milestones.md:97:| 11 | Add hybrid morphology classes | Shared leaning programming (60/40) | Jack lead | Surface / skeleton / point neuron mix |\ndocs/milestones.md:98:| 12 | Define readouts and task layer | Shared leaning math-physics (45/55) | Shared lead | Quantitative outputs and task metrics |\ndocs/milestones.md:99:| 13 | Build the validation ladder | Math/physics-heavy (30/70) | Grant lead | Numerical \\+ biological sanity checks |\ndocs/milestones.md:103:| 17 | Extend to whole-brain context views | Programming-heavy (75/25) | Jack lead | Context graph around the active visual circuit |\ndocs/milestones.md:119:**Morphology-resolved surface dynamics constitute an additional intraneuronal computational degree of freedom, capable of shaping circuit input-output transformations through distributed spatiotemporal state on neuronal structure.**\ndocs/milestones.md:123:**In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.**\ndocs/milestones.md:130:* surface-localized inputs on explicit T4/T5 morphology regions  \ndocs/milestones.md:131:* surface propagation over a morphology graph  \ndocs/milestones.md:145:* **`P0`**: canonical point baseline using passive leaky linear non-spiking single-compartment neurons matched to the same circuit and readout  \ndocs/milestones.md:151: In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.\ndocs/milestones.md:154: It should add distributed, morphology-bound intraneuronal state and nothing else that can trivially explain the result.\ndocs/milestones.md:160: The same stimulus driving the same circuit in two models, producing a small but real output difference that shrinks or disappears when geometry is shuffled.\ndocs/milestones.md:173:* **Strong:** the shared-readout change shrinks or disappears when morphology or synapse topology is shuffled  \ndocs/milestones.md:179:2. **`10–25 s`**: split screen with matched point baseline on the left and surface model on the right for the same T4/T5-centered circuit  \ndocs/milestones.md:187:* split view showing baseline scalar activity versus surface-state activity on morphology  \ndocs/milestones.md:188:* shared output trace overlay for the same circuit and stimulus  \ndocs/milestones.md:220:  * task-level differences  \ndocs/milestones.md:251:## **Milestone 2 — Lock the circuit boundary**\ndocs/milestones.md:258:Choose and freeze the smallest scientifically defensible circuit boundary for the first real simulation pass.\ndocs/milestones.md:260:### **Locked circuit decision**\ndocs/milestones.md:303:* LPi/LPTC inventory or wide-field tangential-cell circuitry  \ndocs/milestones.md:318:Promote additional circuitry only when it becomes the leading limitation:\ndocs/milestones.md:345:* both of you can explain why this boundary is sufficient for the first morphology-sensitive test  \ndocs/milestones.md:440:## Milestone 5 — Build the geometry ingestion and multiresolution morphology pipeline\ndocs/milestones.md:489:Turn neuron surfaces into simulation-ready numerical objects.\ndocs/milestones.md:521:- propagation on the surface is numerically stable  \ndocs/milestones.md:689:The wave model is far more convincing if the exact same circuit can be run in:\ndocs/milestones.md:760:- specifying what behaviors are physically meaningful vs numerical artifacts\ndocs/milestones.md:771:## Milestone 11 — Add hybrid morphology classes\ndocs/milestones.md:807:## Milestone 12 — Define readouts and task layer\ndocs/milestones.md:846:- at least one task metric is automated  \ndocs/milestones.md:851:## Milestone 13 — Build the validation ladder\ndocs/milestones.md:886:- stable task outputs  \ndocs/milestones.md:980:- shuffled morphology  \ndocs/milestones.md:1055:Show where the active visual circuit sits inside the larger female brain context.\ndocs/milestones.md:1147:- one end-to-end input frame reaches the chosen circuit\ndocs/milestones.md:1205:8. one “wow” morphology activity visualization\ndocs/milestones.md:1256:- task readouts  \ndocs/milestones.md:1288:- designing the validation ladder  \ndocs/milestones.md:1311:12. Milestone 13  \ndocs/milestones.md:1321:- a **Grant vs Jack task board**  \ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:31:from flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_contract import (\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:36:from flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_runtime import (\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:39:    resolve_morphology_runtime_from_arm_plan,\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:40:    run_morphology_runtime_shared_schedule,\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:45:    from tests.test_hybrid_morphology_runtime import _build_surface_skeleton_arm_plan\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:47:    from test_hybrid_morphology_runtime import _build_surface_skeleton_arm_plan\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:77:            runtime = resolve_morphology_runtime_from_arm_plan(arm_plan)\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:78:            _, result = run_morphology_runtime_shared_schedule(\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:95:            self.assertEqual(family[\"source_morphology_class\"], SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS)\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:96:            self.assertEqual(family[\"target_morphology_class\"], SKELETON_NEURON_CLASS)\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:139:            runtime = resolve_morphology_runtime_from_arm_plan(arm_plan)\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:140:            _, result = run_morphology_runtime_shared_schedule(\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:195:            runtime = resolve_morphology_runtime_from_arm_plan(arm_plan)\ntests/test_mixed_coupling_routing.py:196: 