# Subset-selection contract\\n\\nMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\\n`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\\n\\n- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\\n- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\\n- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\\n- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\\n- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\\n\\nThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\\nso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\\n\\n### Geometry handoff contract\\n\\nMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\\n`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\\nfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\\n`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\\n\\nPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\\n\\n- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\\n- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\\n- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\\n\\nThe processed graph archives intentionally separate fine and coarse data:\\n\\n- the surface graph stores the simplified mesh vertices/faces, sparse surface adjacency/Laplacian arrays, and `surface_to_patch` so every surface vertex has an explicit coarse patch assignment\\n- the patch graph stores sparse coarse adjacency/Laplacian arrays plus `patch_sizes`, `patch_centroids`, `patch_seed_vertices`, and CSR-style `member_vertex_indices` / `member_vertex_indptr` arrays for reconstructing patch membership deterministically\\n\\n`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\\nmaterialization version, meshing-config snapshot, and per-root asset\\nstatuses/paths. Raw fetch runs also record `raw_asset_provenance` per\\nroot ID so cache hits, refetches, skips, validation failures, and\\noptional skeleton fetch errors can be audited without reading console\\nlogs. Processed bundle records also expose `artifact_sources` so each\\nsimplified mesh, surface graph, patch graph, and sidecar points back to\\nthe raw mesh and skeleton inputs it was built against.\\n\\nDescriptor and QA rationale:\\n\\n- `docs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md` documents the default `meshing.qa_thresholds`\\n  profile, what each descriptor bucket is meant to capture, and which failed\\n  checks should block downstream use by default.\\n\\nCompatibility shim:\\n\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\\n  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\\n  sidecar name during migration.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-001_Freeze_a_versioned_operator_bundle_contract_and_discretization_design_note/stdout.jsonl:30:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_14\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"_asset_contract_version|bundle_version|processed_graph_path|surface_graph_path|patch_graph_path|meta_json_path|artifact_sources|raw_asset_provenance|operator\\\" src tests scripts docs -S'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"docs/pipeline_notes.md:57:statuses/paths. Raw fetch runs also record `raw_asset_provenance` per\\ndocs/pipeline_notes.md:60:logs. Processed bundle records also expose `artifact_sources` so each\\ndocs/milestones.md:18:- **Math/physics-heavy** \\\\= model formulation, numerical operators, stability, wave equations, discretization choices, validation metrics, analysis design  \\ndocs/milestones.md:37:  - operator format  \\ndocs/milestones.md:65:- define operators and coupling  \\ndocs/milestones.md:92:| 6 | Construct surface discretizations and operators | Math/physics-heavy (30/70) | Grant lead, Jack implements | Laplacians, patch graphs, transfer operators |\\ndocs/milestones.md:481:## Milestone 6 — Construct surface discretizations and operators\\ndocs/milestones.md:500:- fine-to-coarse transfer operators\\ndocs/milestones.md:507:- operator test harnesses  \\ndocs/milestones.md:508:- visualization of operator outputs on meshes\\ndocs/milestones.md:513:- deciding whether to use graph-based or mesh-based operators  \\ndocs/milestones.md:516:- checking whether the operator is faithful enough to the intended physics\\ndocs/milestones.md:522:- coarse and fine operators can be compared  \\ndocs/milestones.md:523:- operator quality metrics exist\\ndocs/milestones.md:867:- operator correctness  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1113:- operator implementation support for Milestone 6  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1119:- operator design  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1125:- agree on the state representation and operator API\\ndocs/milestones.md:1224:### 2\\\\. Operator contract\\ndocs/milestones.md:1228:- per-neuron operators  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1230:- transfer operators  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1287:- keeping the operators and coupling scientifically honest  \\ndocs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md:9:Milestone 6 operator work and Milestone 11 hybrid-morphology work have a shared\\ndocs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md:36:| `simplified_surface_area_rel_error` | `0.15` | `0.30` | yes | Gross area drift changes membrane-scale operator weights. |\\ndocs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md:57:  invalidate downstream operator construction\\ndocs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md:65:Milestone 6 will likely add operator-aware checks such as Laplacian-spectrum\\ndocs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md:66:drift, geodesic path distortion, or transfer-operator residuals. Milestone 11\\nscripts/03_build_wave_assets.py:138:                raw_asset_provenance=existing_record.get(\\\"raw_asset_provenance\\\"),\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py:116:        raw_asset_provenance: dict[str, object] = {}\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py:128:            raw_asset_provenance = dict(fetch_outputs[\\\"raw_asset_provenance\\\"])\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py:131:            raw_asset_provenance = dict(exc.raw_asset_provenance)\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py:140:            raw_asset_provenance=raw_asset_provenance,\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py:148:            asset_provenance = raw_asset_provenance.get(asset_key, {})\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:16:    GEOMETRY_ASSET_CONTRACT_VERSION,\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:44:        self.assertEqual(bundle_paths.surface_graph_path, (ROOT / \\\"data/processed/graphs/101_graph.npz\\\").resolve())\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:45:        self.assertEqual(bundle_paths.patch_graph_path, (ROOT / \\\"data/processed/graphs/101_patch_graph.npz\\\").resolve())\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:80:            raw_asset_provenance={\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:94:        self.assertEqual(manifest[\\\"_asset_contract_version\\\"], GEOMETRY_ASSET_CONTRACT_VERSION)\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:96:        self.assertEqual(manifest[\\\"101\\\"][\\\"bundle_version\\\"], GEOMETRY_ASSET_CONTRACT_VERSION)\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:101:            manifest[\\\"101\\\"][\\\"artifact_sources\\\"][\\\"surface_graph\\\"][\\\"raw_mesh_path\\\"],\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:105:            manifest[\\\"101\\\"][\\\"artifact_sources\\\"][\\\"surface_graph\\\"][\\\"raw_skeleton_status\\\"],\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:108:        self.assertEqual(manifest[\\\"101\\\"][\\\"raw_asset_provenance\\\"][RAW_MESH_KEY][\\\"fetch_status\\\"], FETCH_STATUS_CACHE_HIT)\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:109:        self.assertEqual(manifest[\\\"101\\\"][\\\"processed_graph_path\\\"], str(bundle_paths.surface_graph_path))\\ntests/test_geometry_contract.py:110:        self.assertEqual(manifest[\\\"10