m consumers can discover operator assets without hardcoded filenames, and add a markdown design note that compares the viable discretization families before committing to the default. The design note should be decisive: pick the default fine-surface discretization, explain when fallback behavior is allowed, state which quantities should be conserved or damped, and record the stability-relevant assumptions the later wave engine will inherit.\ndocs/operator_qa.md:175:- if pulse mass or energy checks fail, treat the bundle as numerically unstable\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T133842Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/stdout.jsonl:4:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’m inspecting the existing contract and simulator-planning code first so I can place the hybrid-morphology contract in the current library structure instead of inventing a parallel path.\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260322T133842Z/FW-M11-001_Freeze_a_versioned_hybrid-morphology_contract_fidelity_taxonomy_and_approximation_design_note/stdout.jsonl:6:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'pwd && rg --files'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo\\nscripts/04_validate_manifest.py\\nscripts/11_milestone8a_readiness.py\\nscripts/10_stimulus_bundle.py\\nscripts/run_simulation.py\\nscripts/build_registry.py\\nscripts/08_coupling_inspection.py\\nscripts/01_select_subset.py\\nscripts/00_verify_access.py\\nscripts/05_preview_geometry.py\\nscripts/07_milestone6_readiness.py\\nscripts/17_visualize_simulator_results.py\\nscripts/run_agent_tickets.py\\nscripts/09_milestone7_readiness.py\\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py\\nscripts/14_milestone9_readiness.py\\nscripts/15_surface_wave_inspection.py\\nscripts/03_build_wave_assets.py\\nscripts/02_fetch_meshes.py